What this example actually shows is the ludicrous home advantage of MLS. If the game was played on spreadsheets, they could almost simulate it in a bubble by having the "road team" play down a man. Obviously this isn't a suggestion and there is more than what's on the spreadsheet

So, the numbers come out to a 1.2 expected points value for a home team being down a man all game and 0.9 for a road game. Of course, this example is extreme and we can't measure things like confidence of a road team in this situation or panic of a home team.
